Here’s a minimal Angular 8-ready codebase structure for a dark, photography/videography portfolio with carousels and a clean light-on-dark aesthetic. You can plug this into a fresh `ng new` project and adjust assets.

***

## 1. Project structure

Key pieces:

- `app.component` – shell layout, global dark background.
- `header` – name + nav.
- `hero` – big intro carousel.
- `portfolio` – image + video carousels (pure CSS/TS, no external libs).
- `contact` – simple contact section.

You can split into separate components later; I’ll keep it in one `app` for easier copy-paste.

***

## 2. app.module.ts

Make sure `BrowserModule` and `CommonModule` are present; no external carousel libs needed.

```ts
// src/app/app.module.ts
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';

import { AppComponent } from './app.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [AppComponent],
  imports: [BrowserModule, CommonModule],
  providers: [],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule {}
```

